    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels at MRL 2. Six factors scoped as not-assessed consistent with MRL 2 requirements. Predicted RH = 0.81 < 1.0 acceptance criterion at worst-case operating point. Pressure-rise and shear-stress validation results include structured UQ. The impeller-exit flow symmetry result notes qualitative treatment of cycle-to-cycle aleatory variability; this is judged acceptable given the 4.1% RMS agreement and the secondary nature of this QOI relative to the primary NIH acceptance criterion. Overall credibility sufficient for a Class II 510(k) submission at Medium assurance level.",
